Bandits engaging in renewed attacks on communities in Anka Local Government Area, Zamfara State, killed over 13 persons. While the police gave the figure of casualties in the fresh attack as 13, residents of the invaded communities said that 15 persons were killed by the banditos.
The communities invaded by the bandits were identitied to include Kadaddaba, Rafin Gero, and Babban Baye, in Anka Local Government Area, Zamfara State.
The Police Public Relations Officer of the Zamfara State Command, Muhammadu Shehu, had confirmed the incident.
